item.title: Crabgrass Creek Hike
item.description:
Crabgrass Creek Hike

The club will be going on a 7-mile-long hike in Triple N Ranch. The trailhead for this route is located on Road 1 to Roolp Road. The beginning of the route takes the Orange and Blue trail and follows along the western branch of Crabgrass Creek. The route returns by way of the Blue Trail (sometimes blazed as yellow) to Loop Road and back to Road 1. There are many wonderful wildlife spotting opportunities in the area. This hike will take around 3 - 5 hours, depending on group speed. Bringing multiple containers of water is not only encouraged, but required for participation in this hike. Parking is available. We will be meeting at the SUB at 8:45AM and leaving at 9 AM. We will be meeting at the hiking trail at 9:45AM.

From Saturday, February 10, 2024 9:45 AM to 2:00 PM EST at Triple N Ranch .

item.title: Relay for Event
item.description:
Relay for Event

Join us as we band together for a cure at this year's Relay for Life event at Florida Tech! 

This family-friendly event has activities for everyone to enjoy. Together, we will honor cancer survivors and caregivers, remember those we have lost, and fight against cancer! Relay for Life is more than just a fundraising walk; it's a community event that brings together passionate supporters who embody the American Cancer Society's vision to end cancer as we know it for everyone. This volunteer-led experience unites communities to celebrate cancer survivors, remember loved ones lost to cancer, and raise funds to improve the lives of people with cancer and their families through advocacy, research, and patient support to ensure everyone has an opportunity to prevent, detect, treat, and survive cancer. 
 
To attend the event, please register at https://secure.acsevents.org/site/STR?pg=entry&fr_id=108110. We hope to see you at this year's Relay as we spread hope and raise funds to support the American Cancer Society.

From Saturday, February 17, 2024 11:00 AM to 3:00 PM EST at Crawford Greens.

item.title: WISE "Farther Together" Professional Day
item.description:
WISE "Farther Together" Professional Day

The Women in Science and Engineering program of the Air Force Technical Applications Center is hosting WiSE 2024. All genders are encouraged to participate, value, and pursue science, technology, engineering, and math-related courses in school or college and move on to related careers and progress. The WiSE 2024 symposium theme is "Farther Together" and will feature new and exciting STEM demonstrations from scientists, leaders, and professionals from across the Space Coast. Students will have the opportunity to learn about a wide array of scientific disciplines and potential career paths through one-on-one interaction with government civilians, the Department of Defense, and industry professionals.

The symposium's speaker list includes a very distinguished group of presenters including: Dr. Stacey A. Dixon, Principal Deputy Director of National Intelligence, Ms. Janet Petro, Director Kennedy Space Center, Ms. Corey Hinderstein, Deputy Administrator for Defense Nuclear Nonproliferation, DoE, our own Dr. Toby Daly-Engel, Professor at Florida Institute of Technology, Colonel James Finlayson, Commander, Air Force Technical Applications Center, Brigadier General Jennifer Hammerstedt, Director of Logistics, Engineering, and Force Protection, ACC, Colonel Angelina Maguinness, Commander of 17th Training Wing, Goodfellow FB, Ms. Sarah Mineiro, CEO Tanagra Enterprise, Colonel Kristen Thompson, Commander of 55th Wing, and Dr. Theresa E. Watson, Deputy Chief Scientist, Air Force Technical Applications Center (AFTAC).

Registration is FREE - https://www.wiseusaf.com/register.html

Location:  Space Coast Health Foundation is 1100 Rockledge Blvd, Rockledge, Fl 32955.

Event Date:   March 12, 2024    Check-in Time:   8:00 AM

From Tuesday, March 12, 2024 8:00 AM to 4:30 PM EDT at Space Coast Health Foundation.

item.title: Alternative Spring Break
item.description:
Alternative Spring Break

Spend your Spring Break giving back with Florida Tech's Alternative Spring Break program! This year, our Alternative Spring Break trip focuses on affordable housing, and our trip location will be Key West, Florida. We will partner with Habitat for Humanity of Key West and the Lower Keys to help them achieve their mission of providing everyone a "decent, safe, and affordable place to live." Habitat for Humanity will match participant's interests to service activities. Potential service activities include, but are not limited to, house construction, demolition, painting, landscaping, administrative assistance, etc. Lodging for students attending the trip will be through a local church. Students and a staff chaperone will use bunk beds, a bathroom with a shower, and a full kitchen to prepare meals. During the evenings, participants can learn more about the Key West community and explore local attractions.

 

To apply for this program, please fill out the application using this link: https://floridatech.campuslabs.com/engage/submitter/form/start/621837

For any questions, please attend an ASB Infosession or email civic@fit.edu. 

From Saturday, March 23, 2024 12:00 PM to Thursday, March 28, 2024 1:00 PM EDT at Key West, FL.
